Methods

(static) deleteData()

deleteData.
  • This is an asynchronous call, it will return immediately.
  • If get successfully, following event will be emit:
    ECGUSBModule.Event_Notify("event_notify_ecgusb")
    The key and value will be as below:
    KeyValue
    actionECGProfileModule.ACTION_DELETEDATA_ECGUSB("ACTION_DELETEDATA_ECGUSB")
    ECGProfileModule.ACTION_DELETEDATA_ECGUSB("ACTION_DELETEDATA_ECGUSB")
  • Attention, if you want to be notified, it is mandatory to call following method before you call this method:
    DeviceEventEmitter.addListener(ECGProfileModule.Event_Notify, function (e: Event){});

(static) syncData()

SyncTime.
  • This is an asynchronous call, it will return immediately.
  • If get successfully, following event will be emit:
    ECGUSBModule.Event_Notify("event_notify_ecgusb")
    The key and value will be as below:
    KeyValue
    actionECGProfileModule.ACTION_SYNCDATA_ECGUSB("ACTION_SYNCDATA_ECGUSB")
    ECGProfileModule.ACTION_STARTSYNCDATA_ECGUSB("ACTION_STARTSYNCDATA_ECGUSB")
    ECGProfileModule.ACTION_SYNCDATAINFO_ECGUSB("ACTION_SYNCDATAINFO_ECGUSB")
    ECGProfileModule.DATAINFO("DATAINFO")
    ECGProfileModule.ACTION_FINISHSYNCDATA_ECGUSB("ACTION_FINISHSYNCDATA_ECGUSB")
    ECGProfileModule.ACTION_SYNCDATAPROGRESS_ECGUSB("ACTION_SYNCDATAPROGRESS_ECGUSB")
    ECGProfileModule.PROGRESS("PROGRESS")
  • Attention, if you want to be notified, it is mandatory to call following method before you call this method:
    DeviceEventEmitter.addListener(ECGProfileModule.Event_Notify, function (e: Event){});
